Array.                collection
Fixed size            Growable
Better performance    Relatively less
Homogeneous data      can be heterogeneous
Primitives+objects     Objects only

//Colection-used to represent a Group of object as a single entity.

Collection(I)
-Methods
  int size() --->returns size
  boolean isEmpty();
  boolean contains(Object o)
  Iterator<E> iterator()-->Returns an iterator over the elements in this collection
  Object[] toArray(); --->returns array of all elements in collection
  boolean remove(Object o);
  boolean containsAll(Collection<?> c);
  boolean addAll(Collection<? extends E> c)
  boolean removeAll(Collection<?> c)
  boolean retainAll(Collection<?> c)---->removes from this collection all of its elements that are not contained in the specified collection.
  void clear()--Removes all of the elements from this collection
  
